<item>
            <title>[LU-2985] e2fsck fails and aborted if it generates the database for lfsck</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2985</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The customer&apos;s MDT crashed and they ran e2fsck and a lot of problem couldn&apos;t be fixed. They upgraded e2fsck to latest version and fixed corruptions with it and they are now going to lfsck before mount MDT.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, when they ran e2fsck to generage database, we saw the following error messages and can&apos;t generate database from MDT.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;/sbin/e2fsck -n -v --mdsdb /tmp/mdsdb /dev/ExHwRaid10VolGroup/mdt&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;MDS: got 4168 bytes = 521 entries in lov_objids&lt;br/&gt;
MDS: max_files = 288784110&lt;br/&gt;
MDS: num_osts = 521&lt;br/&gt;
mds info db file written&lt;br/&gt;
db-&amp;gt;put failed&lt;br/&gt;
: DB_KEYEXIST: Key/data pair already exists&lt;br/&gt;
e2fsck: aborted&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Lustre-2.1.0 CentOS5.5</environment>
        <key id="18000">LU-2985</key>
            <summary>e2fsck fails and aborted if it generates the database for lfsck</summary>
